To prepare for the new Modern Warfare i started off with the one that kicked the series into new heights. Bare in mind I played the remaster version. This is a solid game even in today standards. A short but impactful campaign that has good Characters  great set pieces and tight gameplay. In terms of arcade action you can't get any better then this. The multiplayer is as good as it's always been with the creating a class and adding attachments and skins. There are problems of course. First off the loot box system is horrible. I hate it and screw Activision for putting it in here and screw them harder for making dlc maps for a remaster...dlc. Activision really don't care. And for me I played it through veteran and I get it. It's hardest difficulty but you do sometimes feel really unfair. I lost count how many times I'd fight the same enemy after a checkpoint restart and it always be random if I'd have time to shoot him or he'd snap to me and kill me quicker then I can aim down sight's. Our felt very unfair. Apart from that the game is great and set in stone a series that would make way for a generation of gamers. But what did you guys and gals think? Let me know and I'll see you guys... In the next post.  #game #Games #gaming #videogame #videogames #callofduty #callofduty4modernwarfare #callofduty4remastered

Finally it's #backlogbattler time and this time it's Fist of the North Star Lost Paradise on PS4. A game where you play as Kenshiro in another non canon adventure where knowing characters does help. In the tutorial you take out Shin  then go to the city of Eden where you become it's protector. You befriend the captain of the guard  get a truck you can ride around the sandbox in  do odd jobs like bartending  healing and managing a host club. You get random battles with goons everywhere which build up exp. You get references to the anime and manga everywhere. It's a wander around fighty drivey smash people's skulls in affair that plays a lot like Yakuza. It's mindless and can rack up the time easily. It's a fun game and if you like the series you'll love it. If you allow things to get on top of you however the main story will take a back seat and you'll find yourself just wandering around or driving around the desert looking for people to kill and items to get in the wastes. It's a fun game and I think it's worth the Â£30 asking price. #sega #sony #gaming #gamer #retro #arcade #franchise #retrocollectiveeurope #pickups #3d #adventure #rpg #action #3d #atlus #fistofthenorthstar #hokutonoken #kenshiro #playstation #ps4 #gamestergram #videogames #gamersunite #gamecollector #gamersofinstagram #jackrabbitgamer

ğŸ® BARCODE BATTLERS II æ™‚ç©ºã‚’è¶…ãˆãŸæˆ¦å£«ãŸã¡ (Warriors who travelled in time) . Barcode Battlers was a series of Handheld consoles made by Epoch. . Barcode scanning toys and arcade games were extremely popular in the 90's Japan including the Datach Famicom add on  the later Digivices and Barcode Wars by Bandai. The strength of the Barcode Wars series was its connection to nintendo  allowing them to make exclusive barcode games with nintendo franchise such as Mario Bros and Zelda. . It also allowed players connect to their Super Famicom or original Gameboy via the 'Barcode Boy' to send data from the barcode cards into the Barcode Battler console games. . Barcode Battler was highly successful in Japan and even saw a release of western versions with alternative art and characters. . Did you go to the eshop and download yourself a copy of Gold Silver or Crystal?  Only getting the Red Gyradose as your first shiny? And want more?  What if i told you that in Gen 2 you can breed a shiny with a non shiny Pokemon Turning your odds from 1/8192 to 1/64 through breeding? --- Shiny hunting feels impossible through gen 2 and onward to some of us because of how high the odds are and theres no shiny charm till black and white 2.  Well In gen 2 theres something in the coding that makes Breeding a shiny with a mon shiny pop out shinies a bit faster  I believe its only breeding males with females of the same species or egg group  Anyway.  So you may not have a shiny ditto yet  Theres two ways to get one Random encounter one Or Use your red gyradose to trade to red blue or yellow use on a ditto only with mimic then catch and trade back to gsc  If you just have the Shiny Gyradose what can you breed with it?  One example is Dragonair  Another Tentacruel  A helpful thing to know is your egg groups  Gyradose is in the Water 2 and dragon egg group Dragonair is in the Dragon egg group Ekans is in the field and dragon egg group Tentacruel is in the water 2 egg group Ekans can breed with any field egg group mon such as mankey and primeape even eevee  I have done this shiny hunt method myself Getting myself various Shiny Pokemon  Since theres no abilities eggs will hatch relatively slow  Some hatch faster than others such as Magikarp hatching faster than lapras or snorlax  So my suggestion is trying magikarp first test your patience Then try Dratini or Something else.  If you're like "woah shit is this true?" Ever pick up a used copy of  Black  white  black 2 and white 2 and ever look at them like "Man i wish i could get the old event mons/items"  Well...what if i told you that In 2019 (2020) you can access them.  With 1 simple non game breaking/ bricking system exploit.  Called: the Dns server trick. This can be preformed with a 3ds family system and can also work for the original ds family line (not dsi line) ------ Without further adu gen 5. How to preform the trick: Step one: Go into your Wi-Fi settings  Step 2. Change the dns settings on your primary Wi-Fi connection Only the primary settings and insert these numbers 164.132.44.106.Â  Then hit okay and you're done! ---- You can preform this trick with gen 4 but it requires alot more effort that is difficult for me to explain so i have provided a link in my bio for how to do gen 4. ---- What mystery gifts can you get for gen 5?  Well....the mythicals for that gen. For black and white the liberty ticket to get victini Bw2 to get genesect Every single gen 5 Wi-Fi event is available  Even the Japanese  or other country events Note: the events are randomized and some will duplicate so its a gamble to get them all If you have missed any events  or wanted to relive nostalgia then this is the trick for you! These events can be transfered up to gen 7 through pokebank.  Also note for gen 4: if you get the Arceus  Shaymin and darkrai event they can be soft reset to get shiny  This also works for pokemon ranger shadow of almia and guardian signs to get the manaphy egg event mission ------ #pokemon #Bringbacknationaldex #grookey #sobble #scorbunny  #bea #allister #nessa #milo #drednaw #corviknight #wooloo #pokemonsword #pokemonshield  #pokemonswordshield #gamefreak #nintendoswitch #videogame #videogames #grookeygang #sobblesquad #scorbunnysquad #gamefreak  #nintendo #squirtle #curry #squirtlesquad #alcremie #nintendoswitch

Review Summary- Control ===================== SCORE: 9.1 ===================== You looking for a paranormal  sci-fi action game? This is the game for you! I can guarantee you haven't played anything quite like this before.  It has such a unique style and atmosphere  it oozes mystique  and has a certain stillness that keeps you on edge. It's reminiscent of the old Stanley Kubrick classics  so it wouldn't surprise me if that's where they got their inspiration from.  The combat is some of the most fun you'll have this year. Both the gunplay and psychic abilities are polished and each battle is a thrill. You'll always leave the battlefield in a state of choas  thanks to the destructible environments.  The story is full of mystery and will keep you invested  even if it can be a bit confusing at times  especially with the in-game terminology. Extra lore is told through an excessive amount of collectibles  so while there is a lot to learn about this fascinating world  you're constantly stopping to read yet again. It disrupts gameplay and I do wish it was handled more efficiently.  The side missions are just as much of a standout as the main story  with each one containing an interesting and unique storyline  and I always looked forward to each one.  Exploration was one of the weaker elements of the game  as it did get a little frustrating at times getting to where you needed to go. But this was made up by the amount of hidden secrets (and even some good puzzles) scattered around each area.  While it's a relatively short game  I still recommend this to anyone  as it's one of the better games this year. Plus I managed to score the platinum trophy for it  so that's always a bonus! . #control #remedyentertainment #505games #ps4 #playstation4 #playstation #xboxone #xbox #nintendo #nintendoswitch #switch #gamers #gamer #gaming #gaminglife #gamingcommunity #videogames #review #reviews #gamereview #gamingreview #blog #gamingblog #gameswhisperer  Check out my gaming partners and their awesome content:  @lanpartyentertainment  @gameandscotch @7daysaweekblog @royalsunset54 @hitbtojump @gamer_spark_blogger_  @nintygamer @atfirstplay_gaming  @ca_gaming1415

On-going review- Control ==================== My last post before I wrap up my review tomorrow. Now I've been mostly positive about this game so far  but it's not perfect  and there were a couple of things that held it back from true greatness.  I already talked about the excessive amounts of collectibles in my last post. It's fine to have a lot of extra lore  but surely there was a more efficient way to go about it.  My other main issue was how useless the map was. Maybe use it as a rough guide  but not to go exactly where you need to go. A lot of areas are multi-story  and the map just shows everything in one clump. If you're trying to get from one room to another  the map be more misleading than anything  and I did get frustrated quite a few times trying to get around.  When you think of maps from other games  like Resident Evil 2  they're laid out so clearly it helps makes exploration more fun because you're not wasting time looking at blank walls where the map says there should a doorway.  But I will admit my criticisms are fairly minor and didn't detract too much from the fun overall. So I must say  upon initial reaction to the ending of Tag  my reaction in my previous post still holds truth. However. - - After lots of reading  listening to radios  and watching YouTube videos  I can not say Tag is a bad map. Its truthfully brilliant once you give it some thought  and delivers a tragic ending no one saw coming. - - I will however  say that Tag is still a disappointing map to what they were building up. All we heard about since origins was â€œThe Great Warâ€. All through Blops4  it seemed to be the main point of focus leading up to Tag  giving most of us the impression we would be participating. Like I had hoped. - - Instead  we were completely thrown for a loop. Given something we just did not expect. So now this beckons the question  was this a bad thing? I dont think so. I actually think on Treyarchâ€™s end  if their resources were as limited as its been rumored  was pretty brilliant. Because they pulled it off. - - Its a beautiful map. A nice reimagination of Call of the Dead  which really was one of my favorite maps ever. The radios are super interesting  the wonder weapons are pretty decent and easy to get  and it really plays like old school zombies. - - The ending makes sense too. Given all things considered and understanding their ultimate sacrifice  it is actually really beautiful. Its sad. It actually does make you think once youâ€™re given more context. Once you understand  there was no way to end the cycle with all them existing. It didnt matter how they changed the future  their existence as a whole was the fracture that threw the very universe into chaos. - - Now i ask you  what do you think? Does anyone else Remember Minecade? Well  if you don't  then I can't say I blame you. Minecade was a server network that was popular in the Java edition of Minecraft for a short while. One of the most popular games on it was Super Craft Bross  which was basically Kit PVP with double jumping and special abilities. Sethbling  a Minecraft YouTuber who specializes in making mechanics and contraptions  was a pretty big face of the server for a while.  However  as time went by  things around the server started to go downhill. Updates for Super Craft Bros. were few and far between. Balancing issues and bugs were rarely if ever  fixed. To make things worse  Minecraft's popularity was in a lull. It was around this time I quit playing on Minecade because the games I liked just weren't fun to play anymore.  Fast forward to now. With Minecraft getting a bit of an extra life when it comes to mainstream popularity  I wondered what Minecade has been up to. Last I checked  they could barely break 50 players  and those players were mostly on a rather basic creative server. When I went to the website  all I found was  well  this. The website is a mess. Iâ€™ve also checked around a few forums and canâ€™t find much.  So. What happened to Minecade? Iâ€™ll keep looking. #minecraft #videogames #videogame #game #gamer #gaming #playstation #ps4 #xbox #xboxone #pc #nintendo #nintendoswitch *puts on detective hat*

Iâ€™ve been steadily picking at 'Fire Emblem Three Houses' for the past month or so and while I admit I havenâ€™t quite finished the game I can say confidently that it is one of my favorites of the year. While I donâ€™t have a ton of experience with the Fire Emblem series it's hard to imagine the diehards finding too much at fault with itâ€™s core gameplay. The turn based â€œrock paper scissorsâ€ battles the series is iconic for are so engaging and addictive to play and beautifully presented. Thereâ€™s something so epic about having the camera rapidly zoom in to the ground level of the battlefield so you can watch your characters duke it out. But I think the crowning achievement of this game is its story and narrative structure. You play as â€œThe Professorâ€ a sort of blank slate character who finds him or herself teaching at a prestigious military academy. In between battles you will fill your time lecturing and getting to know your students (who of course are your soldiers in battles) all the while completing side quests around the school. Itâ€™s essentially a lighter but more focused version of what the Persona series does. Within the first couple hours of play I found myself really caring for my students and motivated to prepare them as effectively as I could so they wouldnâ€™t die in combat (yes perma-death is still a thing if you want it). This along with a storyline that evolves and twists based on your actions and choices makes for an immensely satisfying narrative experience. Well  this was seriously the better part of three houses. It wasn't as good as blue lions but better than Rhea's route  definitely better. Characters were the same of course but with new game plus it was easier to improve their skills and power as well as the support ranks. The story was better 'cause we were the "bad appearing but actually good" guys instead of the other way around (where we fought for the actual villain basically... 'till we killed them too). The Final fight wasn't really satisfying (and way easier than in Rhea's route...)  this was probably the easiest boss fight in Fire emblem I even had... Except every boss fight in fricking Fates. I was also surprised (with an piece of disappointment) what this route did with Dedue  that was something Dedue would literally never do and I really didn't liked how the blue lions were showed. I'm glad that I saved Felix with recruiting him... And Ashe... And Lysithia from Golden Deers too. Speaking of  next and last route Golden Deers  I'm looking forward to the meme house. I beat Linkâ€™s Awakening last night! For the most part it was just as enjoyable as the original 1993 version that was my first 2D Zelda. Though I wouldnâ€™t want it to return  the art style was charming and I did like it! Unfortunately  I do think more new features should have been added. Chamber Dungeons were a let down and figure collecting was pointless. The quality of life improvements were appreciated and I was grateful for more heart containers and seashells to hunt down and add to my total playtime. It may have taken me exactly a month to do so  but I've finally completed the story of 'Astral Chain'. What do I think of this game overall? I think this game is superb. Not only did I really enjoy the combat and over-the-top action sequences; I also found the passive cases very fun. And that's not to mention the awesome aesthetics and exciting sound design (in addition to the many twists and turns I encountered throughout this journey). From chimeric engagements to cat adoption  and from investigative puzzles to selfie taking... a NEURON officer's work is never done.  Looks like the folks over at the 'Devil May Cry' office have some serious competition to face this year... #astralchain #nintendoswitch #platinumgames #akirahoward #nintendo #videogames #characteraction #platinumstandard #femaleprotagonist #neuron #legionis

1 ottobre 1954 IBM annuncia il computer Modello 705 L'IBM 705 Ã¨ un computer di prima generazione  a valvole termoioniche. I primi esemplari vengono consegnati nel 1956. E' una macchina character-oriented (ovvero in cui il terminale comunica con l'elaboratore principale un carattere alla volta  contrariamente a quanto avviene nelle macchine block-oriented  in cui il terminale trasferisce blocchi di dati) con caratteri a 7 bit e parole a 35 bit (per contenere 5 caratteri). Il 705 Modello I viene equipaggiato con una capacitÃ  di archiviazione pari a 20.000 caratteri e costa circa 590.000 dollari. Il modello II e III hanno una capacitÃ  di archiviazione pari  rispettivamente  a 40.000 ed 80.000 caratteri. PuÃ² moltiplicare due numeri composti da dieci cifre in soli .0024 secondi. Il 705 Ã¨ il primo computer distribuito commercialmente ad essere equipaggiato con una memoria a nucleo magnetico. Sostituisce l'IBM 702  che utilizzava una memoria costituita da un complesso di tubi a raggi catodici  in cui la sola unitÃ  aritmetica necessitava di 1.700 tubi a vuoto. #retroday #noiche #1980s #apple #atari #8bit #16bit #commodore #amstrad #msx #retrogaming #nerd #retrocomputer #retro #mac #computerhistory #geek #arcade #retrocomputing #videogames #retrogames #vintagecomputer #zxspectrum #vintage #retroconsole #machenesannoiduemila #AccaddeOggi #OnThisDay

Ieri ho deciso di aprire una nuova specie di rubrica che intitolerÃ² : " Giochi epici che avrei dovuto giocare all'uscita ma che non ho mai giocato fino ad oggi''. Il protagonista di oggi e' Uncharted 4 A Thief's End. Wow. Sono rimasto davvero sorpreso dal prodotto di Naughty Dog  e mai avrei pensato che la saga di Uncharted potesse superare la bellezza e epicitÃ  raggiunta nel 2. Iniziando dai paesaggi   Uncharted 4 spinge PS4 a livelli mai visti primi. E' un gioco bello da vedere ma soprattutto ti dÃ  l' impressione di essere vivo davanti i tuoi occhi. Per non parlare dell' Oceano e di come Naughty Dog abbiato lavorato per renderlo un paradiso per i giocatori. La chiusura delle storie legate a ciascun personaggio e' da Oscar   e ammetto di aver versato un paio di lacrime durante le scene finali. Questo e' l' esempio vivente di come un gioco passi da semplice mezzo di intrattenimento a vera e propria arte. Un applauso  Yesterday I decided to start a new journey which i named: "Epic games that I should have played when they came out but never did until now". Today's protagonist is Uncharted 4 A Thief's End. Wow. I was really surprised by Naughty Dog's product  and I never thought that the Uncharted saga could overcome the beauty and epicness achieved in second game. Starting from the landscapes  Uncharted 4 pushes PS4 to levels never seen before. It is so beautiful that there are times where the game almost seems to gain a life of his own. All the stories related to the different characters are closed wonderfully   and I have to admit that I cried a little during the ending scenes. This is the example of how a simple tool of entertainment can become art. Well done Naughty Dog. #play #playstation #ps4 #videogiochi #videogames #love #cuore #perfetto #uncharted #naughty #dog #nathan #arte #art #perfect #applausi #joy #wonderful #perfetto #likeforlike #follow

Finally it's #backlogbattler time and this time it's Fist of the North Star Lost Paradise on PS4. A game where you play as Kenshiro in another non canon adventure where knowing characters does help. In the tutorial you take out Shin  then go to the city of Eden where you become it's protector. You befriend the captain of the guard  get a truck you can ride around the sandbox in  do odd jobs like bartending  healing and managing a host club. You get random battles with goons everywhere which build up exp. You get references to the anime and manga everywhere. It's a wander around fighty drivey smash people's skulls in affair that plays a lot like Yakuza. It's mindless and can rack up the time easily. It's a fun game and if you like the series you'll love it. If you allow things to get on top of you however the main story will take a back seat and you'll find yourself just wandering around or driving around the desert looking for people to kill and items to get in the wastes. It's a fun game and I think it's worth the Â£30 asking price. #sega #sony #gaming #gamer #retro #arcade #franchise #retrocollectiveeurope #pickups #3d #adventure #rpg #action #3d #atlus #fistofthenorthstar #hokutonoken #kenshiro #playstation #ps4 #gamestergram #videogames #gamersunite #gamecollector #gamersofinstagram #jackrabbitgamer

Pickpocketing is also interesting in this game. You have to get close to a person and while remaing undetected  reach into their pockets.  The timer at the start determines how many seconds you will get to rummage around looking for items. The longer you can hold out the longer you get to look.  As the timer goes up  depending on your skill and your marks various attributes  it gets more dangerous to keep rummaging. The background of the timer will start to turn red when you are close to getting caught.  Once you have completed the timer mini game successfully you use what time you have earned to go through the various items and uncover what they are. You pick what you want and then have to navigate to the exit.  You manage to do that before time runs out and you have successfully pickpocketed someone!  Protip: To level Pickpocketing up faster and easier  do it to people who are sleeping! . . . . . . . . . . #pickpocket #kingdomcomedeliverance #pickpocketing #kingdomcome #medieval #rpg #gaming #videogames #simulation #xboxgamepass #XboxShare #XboxOneX #gamepass #rogue #thief #stealing #ninjaskills

BIONIC COMMANDO: In 1987 arcade gamers became special forces soldiers in order to infiltrate an enemy base and stop the launch of a devastating missile attack.  A classic action platform game from Capcom this is one of the coolest games of its time thanks to all jumping being removed in favour of using an extendable arm to move around the level.  Converted to a ton of home computers including the Amiga  Atari ST  C64  ZX Spectrum and Amstrad CPC this also came to the NES although that version was very different.  Did you ever play this game? It may have taken me exactly a month to do so  but I've finally completed the story of 'Astral Chain'. What do I think of this game overall? I think this game is superb. Not only did I really enjoy the combat and over-the-top action sequences; I also found the passive cases very fun. And that's not to mention the awesome aesthetics and exciting sound design (in addition to the many twists and turns I encountered throughout this journey). From chimeric engagements to cat adoption  and from investigative puzzles to selfie taking... a NEURON officer's work is never done.  Looks like the folks over at the 'Devil May Cry' office have some serious competition to face this year... #astralchain #nintendoswitch #platinumgames #akirahoward #nintendo #videogames #characteraction #platinumstandard #femaleprotagonist #neuron #legionis

Akumajou Dracula X: Chi no Rondo  AKA Castlevania: Rondo of blood.  The game was released in japan on oct 29th  1993. An amazing halloween gift for our Japanese buddies! And it wasn't released outside of Japan for almost 15 years. At some point it was considered the best Castlevania ever  and I think everyone thought alike until Symphony of the Night. So basically  a lost jewell for the western world. There was a remake in the SNES but it was actually a complete different game. It was possible to play it as an unlockable game in The Dracula X Chronicles... But now we are going to be able to enjoy the original game for the first time  on the Turbografx-16 mini!!! So  the first videos are an amazing intro animation. The voice translation is: "Long ago people lived in peace and harmony. No one noticed the looming shadow among them. Their senses clouded in darkness  evil ate away at their souls. In the late hour they congregate to call the powers of Satan with sinful blood to save them from their mortal existence. Evis has once again been made flesh. He can become a bat  fog  or wolf and feasts on human blood. Lord of darkness  master of Castlevania  Dracula walk among us." This game has a fantastic soundtrack  making use of the CD-Rom capacity for better sound quality. There's a 2CD OST released with music from this game and also from Castlevania Bloodlines. 30 settembre 1988 IBM annuncia l'avvenuta spedizione di 3 milioni di personal computer PS/2. Il PS/2 succede alle serie PC  PC/XT e PC/AT ed utilizza la Micro Channel Architecture  un formato di bus incompatibile con lo standard ISA  adottato dai costruttori di cloni. IBM aveva presentato le sue macchine PS/2 solo l'anno prima  facendo in modo che le unitÃ  disco per floppy da 3 pollici e Â½ e la VGA (Video Graphic Array) divenissero degli standard per i computer IBM ed i compatibili. I PS/2 sono stati i primi computer IBM ad utilizzare il chip 80386 di Intel ed il nuovo sistema operativo OS/2  consentendo l'utilizzo di un mouse con i computer IBM. #retroday #noiche #1980s #apple #atari #8bit #16bit #commodore #amstrad #msx #retrogaming #nerd #retrocomputer #retro #mac #computerhistory #geek #arcade #retrocomputing #videogames #retrogames #vintagecomputer #zxspectrum #vintage #retroconsole #machenesannoiduemila #AccaddeOggi #OnThisDay

We had a jammed packed Saturday! Days like this when we go  go  go I worry how Collin is going to function in a new place.  The company Richard works for had a Carnival day for employees and their families. It was a blast! Between food trucks and carnival performers  you can't go wrong.  As always  arriving at a new place it takes Collin a little awhile to get out of the Jeep. We typically set a timer so he knows that once the timer goes off we need to get out of the Jeep. I typically can tell when Collin is anxious about going to a new place because he will start to perseverate on something...today it was snacks.  We did bring his Ipad just in case it was too overwhelming for him. I now have been trained to automatically pick up what will contribute to sensory overload. There were plenty... But we take it at Collin's pace and that seems to work for him. I'm pretty sure he had a good time! He loved the dunk tank and participated in dunking one of Richard's manager and the president of the company ğŸ˜‰  We ended the day with a birthday party for one of Jonah's friends  Liam...friends since VPK!! The party was at a local place called The District - arcade  and bowling! All the kiddos had an amazing time!! It was nice to see Collin like every other kid  having fun playing video games...I definitely could tell after he was done playing games he was starting to have a sensory overload. He was very excited not knowing where to look or what he wanted to play...and he wanted to touch EVERYTHING! He played a handful of games and did really well  but as the evening progressed I could tell he was done. He started stimming  flapping and rocking back and forth. At that point  all the kids had burned through their game cards and it we called it a night and headed home. . . . #autismmoments #autismsiblingsrock #autismlove #differntnotless #autismjourney #autismfamily #asd  #autism #autismacceptance #autismmom #autismdad  #autisminthecommunity #autismstar #autismwarrior  #specialneedsmom #specialneedsparenting #specialneedskids #advocate  #carnivalfun #foodtrucks #zebraballoonanimals #videogames #boutiquebowling #thedistrictoviedo

Today was the day where I said to myself "this is a relax day. Dont go wild about doing ANYTHING today." And I didn't. I got up later than usual  ate breakfast (I dont know what that is anymore so imagine me looking at a cereal bowl whispering questioningly "what is... breakfast.") Barely did makeup  just mascara and lipstick  played ACNL and ANPC  went for a smol stroll and laid back in bed again. I constantly want to do something fun  but at the same time its draining me. Its making my head hurt  making myself tired on purpose and freaking out over everything. When all I need to do sometimes.. is SIT MY ASS DOWN AND GIVE MYSELF A DAY FOR ME. And it felt good. . . . . . #selfcare #relaxed #lazyday #videogames #selfie #its7oclocksomewhere #witchy #tired #stressed #chill #calm #selflove #takingcare #caring #destressing #wiccan #soothing #lazysinday #sundaysinday #kawaiiaf #boldlipstick #chilling #love #smilethrough #sleepy

ğŸ® BARCODE BATTLERS II æ™‚ç©ºã‚’è¶…ãˆãŸæˆ¦å£«ãŸã¡ (Warriors who travelled in time) . Barcode Battlers was a series of Handheld consoles made by Epoch. . Barcode scanning toys and arcade games were extremely popular in the 90's Japan including the Datach Famicom add on  the later Digivices and Barcode Wars by Bandai. The strength of the Barcode Wars series was its connection to nintendo  allowing them to make exclusive barcode games with nintendo franchise such as Mario Bros and Zelda. . It also allowed players connect to their Super Famicom or original Gameboy via the 'Barcode Boy' to send data from the barcode cards into the Barcode Battler console games. . Barcode Battler was highly successful in Japan and even saw a release of western versions with alternative art and characters. . Persona 3 â€“ Beat: 11 November 2007 Time: 129: 30 Persona 3 â€“ The Journey â€“ Beat: 5 November 2010 Time: 64: 11  I remember the summer of 2007. There was no expectation for another release from Atlus. I was already acquainted with the world of Persona and MegaTen  so at that point only Atlus fans and the odd weirdo were looking forward to this.  I had pre-ordered it at GameStop and they didn't get it until Thursday of release week (Games and movies were released on Tuesdays). I played it for a few months and those blue screens and menus and music blended with the long hazy days of late summer  the chilly nights of mid autumn  and the frozen reverberations of winter chill.  I still have mixed feelings about this game. But is it a good game? Yup! I'd play the PSP port in a heartbeat if I find a reasonable priced copy.  #persona3 #persona3fes #persona #atlus #atlususa #megaten #playstation2 #ps2 #PlayStation #jrpg #rpg #roleplayinggames #classicgames #instagaming #videogames #gamecollection #smt #shinmegamitensei #megamitensei

To prepare for the new Modern Warfare i started off with the one that kicked the series into new heights. Bare in mind I played the remaster version. This is a solid game even in today standards. A short but impactful campaign that has good Characters  great set pieces and tight gameplay. In terms of arcade action you can't get any better then this. The multiplayer is as good as it's always been with the creating a class and adding attachments and skins. There are problems of course. First off the loot box system is horrible. I hate it and screw Activision for putting it in here and screw them harder for making dlc maps for a remaster...dlc. Activision really don't care. And for me I played it through veteran and I get it. It's hardest difficulty but you do sometimes feel really unfair. I lost count how many times I'd fight the same enemy after a checkpoint restart and it always be random if I'd have time to shoot him or he'd snap to me and kill me quicker then I can aim down sight's. Our felt very unfair. Apart from that the game is great and set in stone a series that would make way for a generation of gamers. But what did you guys and gals think? Let me know and I'll see you guys... In the next post.  #game #Games #gaming #videogame #videogames #callofduty #callofduty4modernwarfare #callofduty4remastered
